en_223450_0	Three persons have been arrested in connection with a Wallapatta racket in the Knuckles Forest Reserve.
en_223450_1	The suspects were taken into custody by the Forest Conservation Officers during a 48-hour raid yesterday.
en_223450_2	Forest conservation officers took into custody 15 kilograms of Wallapatta and a three-wheeler, worth about Rs.
en_223450_3	1.5 million.
en_223450_4	Initial investigations have revealed that the suspects are residents of Dankanda, Matale and have been involved in this racket for some time.
en_223450_5	They have also been involved in an illegal business of cannabis cultivation and the sale of wild meat.
